<includeonly>{{#ask: [[-Has subobject::{{{page|{{FULLPAGENAME}}}}}]] [[{{{subcat|}}}]]
 | link=none
 | format=template
 | template={{{row-template|Category/subobject-instance}}}
 | userparam={{PAGENAME:{{{subcat|}}}}}
 | sort=Has sort order
 | order=asc
}}</includeonly><noinclude>
Iterates the subobject instances of one type on a given page, rendering
each through a user-supplied row template.

This is a Tier A primitive — it owns the inverse-ask + sort pattern but
delegates per-instance markup to the row template.

Parameters:
* subcat       - The subobject category (e.g. `Category:Chapter`)
* page         - The parent page whose instances should be listed; defaults
                 to {{FULLPAGENAME}}
* row-template - Template to render each instance; defaults to
                 `Category/subobject-instance` (which reuses Category/table).
                 The row template receives the subobject fragment as
                 {{{1}}} (SMW's first positional arg) and the subcategory
                 name (without `Category:` prefix) as {{{#userparam}}}.

Example (default — renders as mini-tables):
 {{Category/subobject-instances|subcat=Category:Chapter|page=MyBook}}

Example (custom card layout):
 {{Category/subobject-instances
   |subcat=Category:Chapter
   |page=MyBook
   |row-template=BookChapterCard
 }}

And Template:BookChapterCard:
 <div class="chapter-card">
   <h3>{{Property/value|prop=Has_chapter_title|page={{{1}}}}}</h3>
   <p>{{Property/value|prop=Has_summary|page={{{1}}}}}</p>
 </div>

Instances are sorted by `?Has sort order` ascending. Override the row
template itself if you need a different sort or filter.
</noinclude>
